  <li><strong>Flaxseed or Chia Seeds:</strong> When mixed with water, these seeds form a gel that works as a fantastic egg replacer. Use one tablespoon of ground flaxseed with three tablespoons of water to replace one egg.</li>
  <li><strong>Plant-Based Milk:</strong> Almond, soy, oat, or coconut milk are ideal substitutes for dairy milk. They blend smoothly into batters and donâ€™t overpower flavors.</li>
  <li><strong>Applesauce or Mashed Bananas:</strong> Both add moisture and a touch of natural sweetness while binding ingredients together.</li>
  <li><strong>Coconut Oil or Vegan Margarine:</strong> These provide the fat necessary for tender baked goods, mimicking the role of butter perfectly.</li>
