<p>These muffins are moist, naturally sweet, and made with simple ingredients.</p>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong>  </p>
<h4><a href="https://www.digistore24.com/redir/525847/Hatemmrabet/"> </a>ðŸ”¥ Love cooking healthy? Grab your copy of Vegan Baking Made Easy and start baking plant-based magic today!</h4><br><br><ul>
<li>2 ripe bananas (mashed)  </li>
<li>1/2 cup maple syrup or agave nectar  </li>
<li>1/4 cup coconut oil (melted)  </li>
<li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract  </li>
<li>1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour  </li>
<li>1 teaspoon baking soda  </li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon salt  </li>
<li>1 teaspoon ground cinnamon (optional)  </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Instructions:</strong><br />
Preheat your oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C). Mix the mashed bananas, sweetener, coconut oil, and vanilla in a large bowl. In another bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture. Pour batter into muffin tins lined with paper cups and bake for 20-25 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean.</p>
<h4>2. Classic Vegan Chocolate Chip Cookies</h4>
<p>These cookies are soft on the inside and lightly crispy on the outside, just like youâ€™d expect.</p>
<h4><a href="https://www.digistore24.com/redir/525847/Hatemmrabet/"> </a>ðŸ”¥ Love cooking healthy? Grab your copy of Vegan Baking Made Easy and start baking plant-based magic today!</h4><br><br><p><strong>Ingredients:</strong>  </p>
