<h4>3. Easy Vegan Lemon Loaf</h4>
<p>Bright and refreshing, this lemon loaf is moist and perfect for afternoon tea.</p>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong>  </p>
<h4><a href="https://www.digistore24.com/redir/525847/Hatemmrabet/"> </a>ðŸ”¥ Love cooking healthy? Grab your copy of Vegan Baking Made Easy and start baking plant-based magic today!</h4><br><br><ul>
<li>1 1/2 cups flour  </li>
<li>1 cup sugar  </li>
<li>1 teaspoon baking powder  </li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon baking soda  </li>
<li>1/4 teaspoon salt  </li>
<li>1 cup almond milk  </li>
<li>1/3 cup vegetable oil  </li>
<li>2 tablespoons lemon juice  </li>
<li>1 tablespoon lemon zest  </li>
<li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract  </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Instructions:</strong><br />
Preheat oven to 350Â°F (175Â°C). Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. In another bowl, combine almond milk, oil, lemon juice, zest, and vanilla extract. Mix wet and dry ingredients until just combined. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake 45-50 minutes. Let cool before slicing.</p>
